xdelta3-gui (26.05) mx; urgency=medium

  * Calculate and show live estimated time to completion and estimated size for the patch
  * Show a clear error message at startup if xdelta3 is not installed
  * Fields now turn red immediately when a file path does not exist
  * Fix: selecting "None" for secondary compression now correctly disables it
  * Automatically suggest an output filename when applying a patch
  * Show the patch file size in the success message after creating a patch
  * Remember the last used folder between file selections
  * Automatically remove incomplete output files if an operation fails or is cancelled
  * Elapsed time now shows hours for operations that take longer than an hour
  * Patch filenames are now always fully descriptive (e.g. 1.0_to_1.1 instead of 1.0_to_1)

 -- Adrian <adrian@mxlinux.org>  Sun, 10 May 2026 20:42:54 -0400

xdelta3-gui (26.02) mx; urgency=medium

  * Improve patch creation/apply reliability for file paths with spaces and special characters
  * Fall back to a valid default compression option when the saved setting is unavailable
  * Make file pickers clearer with dedicated ISO/Delta filters and smoother directory selection
  * Correct user-facing wording in status and error messages
  * Improve default patch naming for version upgrades

